    • Method Detail

      • calculateBaseSignatureString

        public static java.lang.String calculateBaseSignatureString(java.lang.String method,
                                            java.lang.String requestUrl,
                                            java.lang.String baseParameterString)
                                                     throws java.lang.Exception
        Creates the encoded base signature string.
        Parameters:
        method - The HTTP method (GET or POST)
        requestUrl - The URL where the data was sent to or received from
        baseParameterString - The sorted base parameter string containing the OAuth parameters and additional function parameters (e.g. 'date_since=0&max=10')
        Returns:
        An URL encoded string consisting of a combination of the method, the URL and the base parameter string and by URL encoding the result.
        Throws:
        java.lang.Exception

      • calculateSignature

        public static java.lang.String calculateSignature(java.lang.String baseSignatureString,
                                  java.lang.String consumerSecret,
                                  java.lang.String tokenSecret)
                                           throws java.lang.Exception
        Calculates the signature encoding it with HMAC SHA256 and Base64 using the encoded base signature string and the secrets.
        Parameters:
        baseSignatureString - The URL encoded base signature string with method, URL, OAuth parameters and function parameters (e.g. 'date_since=0&max=10')
        consumerSecret - The application secret
        tokenSecret - The access secret
        Returns:
        a short string containing the signature. This signature will be compared on the server side in order to test if the secrets are valid and if the message was not changed during transportation to the server.
        Throws:
        java.lang.Exception - if there was an error calculating the signature (e.g. missing internal methods).

      • checkBasicAuthorization

        public static java.util.Map<java.lang.String,java.lang.String> checkBasicAuthorization(java.lang.String authorization)
                                                                                throws java.lang.Exception
        Do some basic checks on a received authorization string from the server and extract the OAuth parameters.
        Parameters:
        authorization - The complete authorization header string
        Returns:
        A map with name/value pairs of the individual OAuth parameters
        Throws:
        java.lang.Exception - if there was a problem with one of the parameters or the whole OAuth parameter string (e.g. missing parameter).
